cancelAuction(uint256,address).details: Transfers the NFT back to the auction creator and emits an AuctionCanceled event

createAuction(uint256,uint256,address,ui.details: Store the auction details in the auctions mapping and emit an AuctionCreated event. If there is no curator, or if the curator is the auction creator, automatically approve the auction.

createBid(uint256,uint256).details: If provided a valid bid, transfers the provided amount to this contract. If the auction is run in native ETH, the ETH is wrapped so it can be identically to other auction currencies in this contract.

endAuction(uint256).details: If for some reason the auction cannot be finalized (invalid token recipient, for example), The auction is reset and the NFT is transferred back to the auction creator.

createBid(uint256,uint256).notice: Create a bid on a token, with a given amount.

endAuction(uint256).notice: End an auction, finalizing the bid on if applicable and paying out the respective parties.
